data.title: Woody Allen: A Documentary
data.text:
Woody Allen: A Documentary (30-May-2012)

Director: Robert B. Weide

Writer: Robert B. Weide

Keywords: Documentary, Filmmaking, Biography

Groundbreaking documentary provides a uniquely in-depth look into Woody Allen's career, life, and creative process.

ABSTRACT

Billed as the first-ever on-camera depiction of his creative process, Woody Allen: A Documentary follows the iconic New York-based director from his early days as a teenaged comedy writer all the way through to his present standing as a legend in the pantheon of cinematic greats.
